Description:
Oak is a software platform for building distributed systems providing externally verifiable (or falsifiable) claims about system behaviors in a transparent way. Oak provides building blocks that are used to build Enclave Applications, i.e. applications that are isolated from the host on which they run, and are remotely attestable.

Local Modifications:
Added "chromium/proto/*" directory to provide protocol buffer that supports protobuf_lite, which is required by Chromium. The reference to //third_party/protobuf/src/google/protobuf/any.proto in `src/proto/attestation/eventlog.proto` is replaced with a wire-compatible equivalents version of Any because Any cannot be directly imported because it is not in the `protobuf_lite` source and the `protobuf_full` source cannot be included because of its large size. Therefore, we copy the single proto we need from protobuf_full which is small (and stable), this is commonly done in other Chromium directories. All other copied protocol buffers are unchanged. 

